
******************************************************************************
dpcon(options,levels,spacing)	- Display Plotted Contours 
dpconn(options,levels,spacing)	- Display Contours Without Erasing Screen
pcon(options,levels,spacing)	- Plot contours on plotter
******************************************************************************

  The conventional "contour plot" display produced by "dcon" is actually not a
  contour plot, but a "color intensity map". "dpcon" produces a true contour
  plot display, and "pcon" produces a contour plot on the plotter. "levels"
  represents the maximum number of contour levels which will be shown; the
  default value is 4. "spacing" represents the spacing relative intensity
  of successive contour levels; the default spacing is 2. "dpconn" does not
  erase the screen. In phased spectra, the 'pos' option displays positive
  peaks only, the 'neg' option displays negative peaks only. The default
  displays both positive and negative peaks.  The last option is 'noaxis'
  which omits outlining the display (or plot) and omits drawing the
  horizontal and vertical axes.  The options 'pos', 'neg', and/or 'noaxis'
  must precede levels and spacing in the argument list.

  dpcon('axisonly') draws a 2D axis without drawing any data. 
